# SwiftUI Rules

## New Screens: Prefer SwiftUI
For any new screen or flow:
- Implement the primary UI as a SwiftUI `struct` conforming to `View`
- Use SwiftUI navigation, sheets, confirmation dialogs, alerts, and semantic colors
- Keep result screens separate when requirements call for distinct Food, Text, Mixed, and Error screens

## MVVM Separation of Concerns
| Layer | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| **View** | Declarative, thin — layout and bindings only |
| **ViewModel** | User-flow orchestration and UI state (`ObservableObject` + `@Published`, or `@Observable`) |
| **Service** | OCR, ML inference, summarization, image classification, validation, nutrition lookup |

## Async Work & Main-Thread Safety
- Perform API calls, OCR, Core ML, Foundation Models, and heavy work **off** the main thread
- Publish UI-facing state on the **main actor**:
  - Use `.receive(on: DispatchQueue.main)` before mutating `@Published` properties (consistent with other Combine adopters in the project)
  - Or prefer `async/await` with `@MainActor` for new features
- Avoid blocking the main thread inside `View.body` or `onAppear`
- Account for view identity, `.task` / `.onAppear` lifecycle, and **cancellation** when bindings or navigation state changes
